    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If it's the plotting that needs to change, I think that'd be better handled upstream in matplotlib, not pandas.\n\nThere's a bit [here](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15767781/python-matplotlib-way-to-transpose-axes) about doing this. You would need to apply that to each of your subplots, and then adjust the `xlim` and `ylim`.\n\nFinally, you might be able to do this by making the axes ahead of time, and then iterating over the columns. `df` is just a 300 x 15 DataFrame\n\n``` python\nIn [34]: fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=15)\n\nIn [36]: for ax, col in zip(axes, df.columns):\n    ...:     ax.plot(df[col], df.index)\n```\n"
  },
